HEADWORD: Clinometer
<hw>Cli*nom"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>kli`nein</grk> to incline + <ets>-meter</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>An instrument for determining the dip of beds or
strata, pr the slope of an embankment or cutting; a kind of plumb
level.</def> <rj><au>Dana.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Clinometric</ent>⟦br⟧
